<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<t24help xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
    <header>
        <product>PP</product>
		<title>PPT.ERRORLOG</title>
        <table>PPT.ERRORLOG</table>
    </header>
    <overview>
        <ovdesc>
            <p>The purpose of this table is to store all technical errors which are also logged in PPT.HistoryLog table.</p> 
            <p>This is because the PPT.HistoryLog contains also warnings and informative messages, and in order to avoid perfomance issues, the techinical errors will be accessed from this PPT.ErrorLog table.</p>
        </ovdesc>
    </overview>
    <menu>
        <t>
            <field>ID</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Unique ID generated using AUTO.ID.START.</p>
                <p>255 alphanumeric characters.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>CompanyID</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Indicates  the company ID for which the record is created.</p>
                <p>Example: BNK,GB1.</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p> 3 alphanumeric characters (Mandatory Input)</p>
                <p> The value links to the field CompanyID of PPT.COMPANY table.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>Date</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Indicates the Date when the technical error was logged.</p>
                <p>11 characters Date</p>
                <p>It need to be displayed as DD MMM YYYY.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>Timestamp</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Timestamp of the record.</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p> 17 characters Date Time format.</p>
                <p> It need to be displayed as DD MMM YYYY HH:MM:SS.sss.</p>
                <p> Example: 12 JAN 2015 12:34:25.123</p>
                <p> The value is not editable by the user.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>JobName</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Name of the program/procedure/script etc. that runs in error.</p>
                <p>255 alphanumeric characters.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>ProgramName</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Name of the program that logs an event.</p>
                <p>1-255 characters</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>EventType</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Indicates the type of the event that is logged.</p>
                <p>3 characters</p>
                <p>Possible values:</p>
                <p> ERR - Error</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>EventDescription</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Description of the event (warning/error etc.) </p>
                <p>This is a free format text field. Usually it is filled when there is no error code.</p>
                <p>200 characters</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>ErrorCode</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Indicates the Error Code of the event that is logged.</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>   
                <p> 10 characters</p>
                <p> The value links to the field ErrorCode of PPT.ERRORCODE table.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>AdditionalInformation</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Additional Information provided by components in order to detail the event logged.</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p> 256 characters</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
    </menu>
</t24help>
